<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="384" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,942,1329]" pageId="7" pageNumber="384">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,307,942,968]" pageId="7" pageNumber="384">Distribution:</emphasis>
Widespread in the Amazonian region of 
<collectingCountry box="[793,864,942,968]" name="Brazil" pageId="7" pageNumber="384">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, French Guiana, 
<collectingCountry box="[1066,1173,942,968]" name="Suriname" pageId="7" pageNumber="384">Suriname</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1236,1323,942,968]" name="Guyana" pageId="7" pageNumber="384">Guyana</collectingCountry>
(Ribeiro-Júnior &amp; Amaral 2017). In 
<collectingCountry box="[457,567,978,1004]" name="Colombia" pageId="7" pageNumber="384">Colombia</collectingCountry>
there are some records in the eastern Amazonia region, in the departments of 
<collectingRegion box="[151,254,1014,1040]" country="Colombia" name="Guaviare" pageId="7" pageNumber="384">Guaviare</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[308,389,1014,1040]" country="Colombia" name="Vaupes" pageId="7" pageNumber="384">Vaupés</collectingRegion>
(
<figureCitation box="[404,492,1014,1040]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1888,1912]" captionTargetBox="[217,1370,181,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-22@4.[217,1370,181,1864]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4. Distribution maps for the cis-Andean microteiid lizards in Colombia (Alopoglossidae + Gymnophthalmidae). Circles are examined specimens, while squares are records from literature (see Supplementary Files for specific references). Red arrows indicate new records for Colombia. Black arrows show a zoom in to regions where several records overlap. The light green shadow indicates the Orinoco River basin, and the dark green the Amazon River basin." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5681929" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5681929/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="384">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,942,1329]" pageId="7" pageNumber="384">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,389,1050,1076]" pageId="7" pageNumber="384">Similar species:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bonnaterre" baseAuthorityYear="1789" box="[399,603,1050,1076]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Bachia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="7" pageNumber="384" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="flavescens">
<emphasis box="[399,603,1050,1076]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="384">Bachia flavescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may be differentiated from other cis-Andean species of the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Wiegmann" baseAuthorityYear="1856" box="[1304,1437,1050,1076]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Bachia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="7" pageNumber="384" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="heteropa">
<emphasis box="[1304,1437,1050,1076]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="384">B. heteropa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mertens" authorityYear="1972" box="[232,327,1086,1112]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Bachia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="7" pageNumber="384" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="alleni">
<emphasis box="[232,327,1086,1112]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="384">B. alleni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hoogmoed &amp; Dixon" authorityYear="1977" box="[340,491,1087,1112]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Bachia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="7" pageNumber="384" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="guianensis">
<emphasis box="[340,491,1087,1112]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="384">B. guianensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Wiegmann" baseAuthorityYear="1856" box="[504,634,1086,1112]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Bachia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="7" pageNumber="384" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="heteropa">
<emphasis box="[504,634,1086,1112]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="384">B. heteropa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Cope" baseAuthorityYear="1862" box="[647,801,1086,1112]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Bachia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="7" pageNumber="384" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pallidiceps">
<emphasis box="[647,801,1086,1112]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="384">B. pallidiceps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Barbour" authorityYear="1914" box="[814,941,1087,1112]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Bachia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="7" pageNumber="384" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="trinitatis">
<emphasis box="[814,941,1087,1112]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="384">B. trinitatis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Amaral" baseAuthorityYear="1935" box="[1004,1137,1086,1112]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Bachia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="7" pageNumber="384" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bresslaui">
<emphasis box="[1004,1137,1086,1112]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="384">B. bresslaui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group (
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Amaral" baseAuthorityYear="1935" box="[1224,1357,1086,1112]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Bachia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="7" pageNumber="384" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bresslaui">
<emphasis box="[1224,1357,1086,1112]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="384">B. bresslaui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Bachia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="7" pageNumber="384" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cacerensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="384">B. cacerensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1965" box="[255,385,1122,1148]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Bachia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="7" pageNumber="384" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="panoplia">
<emphasis box="[255,385,1122,1148]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="384">B. panoplia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rodrigues, Pavan &amp; Curcio" authorityYear="2007" box="[398,560,1122,1148]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Bachia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="7" pageNumber="384" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="psamophila">
<emphasis box="[398,560,1122,1148]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="384">B. psamophila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kizirian &amp; McDiarmid" authorityYear="1998" box="[572,690,1122,1148]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Bachia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="7" pageNumber="384" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pyburni">
<emphasis box="[572,690,1122,1148]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="384">B. pyburni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vanzolini" authorityYear="1961" box="[750,909,1122,1148]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Bachia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="7" pageNumber="384" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="scolecoides">
<emphasis box="[750,909,1122,1148]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="384">B. scolecoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) in having quadrangular dorsal scales (hexagonal to lanceolate in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Amaral" baseAuthorityYear="1935" box="[369,502,1158,1184]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Bachia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="7" pageNumber="384" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bresslaui">
<emphasis box="[369,502,1158,1184]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="384">B. bresslaui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Wiegmann" baseAuthorityYear="1856" box="[556,686,1158,1184]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Bachia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="7" pageNumber="384" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="heteropa">
<emphasis box="[556,686,1158,1184]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="384">B. heteropa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
groups). See 
<bibRefCitation author="Dixon, J. R." box="[839,992,1158,1184]" pageId="7" pageNumber="384" pagination="1 - 47" refId="ref15925" refString="Dixon, J. R. (1973) A Systematic Review of the Teiid Lizards, Genus Bachia, with Remarks on Heterodactylus and Anotosaura. Miscellaneous publication - University of Kansas, Museum of Natural History, 57, 1 - 47." type="journal article" year="1973">Dixon (1973)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Avila-Pires, T." box="[1004,1214,1158,1187]" pageId="7" pageNumber="384" pagination="1 - 706" refId="ref15408" refString="Avila-Pires, T. (1995) Lizards of Brazilian Amazonia (Reptilia: Squamata). Zoologische Verhandelingen, 299, 1 - 706." type="journal article" year="1995">Ávila-Pires (1995)</bibRefCitation>
, and 
<bibRefCitation author="Ribeiro-Junior, M. A. &amp; da Silva, M. B. &amp; Lima, J. D." pageId="7" pageNumber="384" pagination="148 - 156" refId="ref18359" refString="Ribeiro-Junior, M. A., da Silva, M. B. &amp; Lima, J. D. (2016) A New Species of Bachia Gray 1845 (Squamata: Gymnophthalmidae) from the Eastern Guiana Shield. Herpetologica, 72 (2), 148 - 156. https: // doi. org / 10.1655 / HERPETOLOGICA-D- 15 - 00030" type="journal article" year="2016">
Ribeiro-Júnior 
<emphasis box="[151,207,1194,1220]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="384">et al.</emphasis>
(2016)
</bibRefCitation>
for a detailed description and comparisons.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="384" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,942,1329]" pageId="7" pageNumber="384">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,317,1230,1256]" pageId="7" pageNumber="384">Remarks:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bonnaterre" baseAuthorityYear="1789" box="[324,525,1230,1256]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Bachia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="7" pageNumber="384" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="flavescens">
<emphasis box="[324,525,1230,1256]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="384">Bachia flavescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been suggested as a species complex given its broad morphological variation (
<bibRefCitation author="Kizirian, D. A. &amp; McDiarmid, R. W." box="[159,489,1266,1292]" pageId="7" pageNumber="384" pagination="245 - 53" refId="ref17070" refString="Kizirian, D. A. &amp; McDiarmid, R. W. (1998) A New Species of Bachia (Squamata: Gymnophthalmidae) with Plesiomorphic Limb Morphology. Herpetologica, 54 (2), 245 - 53." type="journal article" year="1998">Kizirian &amp; McDiarmid 1998</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Ribeiro-Junior, M. A. &amp; Amaral, S." box="[502,856,1266,1292]" pageId="7" pageNumber="384" pagination="151 - 196" refId="ref18425" refString="Ribeiro-Junior, M. A. &amp; Amaral, S. (2017) Catalogue of distribution of lizards (Reptilia: Squamata) from the Brazilian Amazonia. IV. Alopoglossidae, Gymnophthalmidae. Zootaxa, 4269 (2), 151 - 196. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4269.2.1" type="journal article" year="2017">Ribeiro-Júnior &amp; Amaral 2017</bibRefCitation>
). Previously, 
<bibRefCitation author="Dixon, J. R." box="[1010,1163,1266,1292]" pageId="7" pageNumber="384" pagination="1 - 47" refId="ref15925" refString="Dixon, J. R. (1973) A Systematic Review of the Teiid Lizards, Genus Bachia, with Remarks on Heterodactylus and Anotosaura. Miscellaneous publication - University of Kansas, Museum of Natural History, 57, 1 - 47." type="journal article" year="1973">Dixon (1973)</bibRefCitation>
suggested that the individuals from 
<collectingCountry box="[301,411,1302,1328]" name="Colombia" pageId="7" pageNumber="384">Colombia</collectingCountry>
belonging to the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bonnaterre" baseAuthorityYear="1789" box="[607,753,1302,1328]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Bachia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="7" pageNumber="384" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="flavescens">
<emphasis box="[607,753,1302,1328]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="384">B. flavescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group may correspond to an undescribed species.
</paragraph>
